== Rice and Chicken ==

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Boil the @water for the rice{300%ml} in a large #saucepan{} over high heat. Stir in half the @chicken stock pot{1/2} and add the @basmati rice{150%g}. Lower the heat to medium. Cook the rice for ~{10%minutes} with the lid on (or use some foil). After 10 mins, remove the pan from the heat and leave the rice for another ~{10%minutes} to finish cooking in its own steam.

While the rice is cooking, peel and grate the @ginger{1} and @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}) and zest the @lime{1}. Pick the @coriander{1}(leaves picked from stalks) from their stalks, roughly chop the leaves and finely chop the stalks (keep separate). Put the @British chicken breasts{2} in a #mixing bowl{} with half the ginger, half the garlic, all the lime zest and all the coriander stalks. Season with a generous pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch}.

Put a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the @desiccated coconut{25%g} (no oil). Toast until golden, ~{4-5%minutes}, stirring frequently. Transfer the coconut to a #small bowl{} and return the pan to high heat with a splash of @?oil{}. Add the chicken and cook until nicely browned, ~{2%minutes} on each side. Transfer the chicken to an #ovenproof dish{}.

Add the remaining @chicken stock pot{1/2} to the frying pan, along with the @water for the chicken{150%ml}. Bring to a boil and stir to dissolve the stock pot. Pour into the ovenproof dish. Wrap the dish tightly with #foil{} and pop it on the top shelf of your oven for ~{16-18%minutes}.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Rinse out the frying pan - we'll use it later for the kale!

== Dressing and Kale ==

While the chicken cooks, cut the lime in half and squeeze the juice into a bowl. Mix in the @ketjap manis{1.5%tbsp}, coriander leaves and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. This is the dressing. Pop your frying pan back on high heat and add a splash of oil. Stir-fry the @kale{100%g} for ~{2%minutes}. Then add the remaining ginger and garlic with a splash of @water{}. Put the lid on and cook for another ~{2-3%minutes}. When done, pour the @soy sauce{1.5%tbsp} over the kale.

== To Serve ==

Fluff the rice up with a #fork{}. Spoon a generous amount into the centre of your bowls and make a well in the middle. Fill each well with kale and sprinkle over the toasted coconut. Carefully remove the chicken from its stock and cut each breast into six slices. Stir 2 tbsp per person of the chicken's cooking liquid into the dressing. Pop the chicken slices on top of the kale and finish with the dressing. Enjoy!